The paper presents an algorithmic solution to a graph problem, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of the term "linear-time algorithm" indicates that it could be in the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The problem of adding edges to a graph to make it biconnected suggests that it could also be in the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper's focus on graph connectivity and optimization suggests that it could be in the category of graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the mention of "protecting sensitive information in statistical tables" suggests that it could be in the category of information theory (cs.IT).
